1
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:47,400
Remember this place?

2
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:48,210
Dailing.

3
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,130
Dailing.

4
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:07,320
Since you're so afraid of pain,

5
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:08,380
don't get a tattoo.

6
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:10,200
Ou Shaowen, get lost.

7
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,560
When did you find out?

8
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:22,440
I always firmly believed

9
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:24,650
that you didn't die.

10
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,920
I asked you out this time

11
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,180
to tell you some things

12
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,130
from the past that you didn't know.

13
00:01:36,759 --> 00:01:38,289
Before I tell you the truth,

14
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:40,960
I hope you are mentally prepared.

15
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:41,560
Tell me.

16
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:46,000
You know everything I've been through.

17
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:48,170
I'm not as fragile as you think.

18
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,320
We all thought Uncle Dai died

19
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:55,520
of a sudden heart attack five years ago.

20
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,200
But he didn't.

21
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:00,500
His medicine was swapped.

22
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,360
I knew it.

23
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,160
He always took his medicine on time.

24
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:17,360
How could he have a sudden heart attack?

25
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,820
It was that bastard Danpa.

26
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,480
To fight for your Dai family's shipping routes back then,

27
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:25,000
he bribed the maid at your house,

28
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,800
Ruannila, to swap the medicine.

29
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:30,240
That's why when Uncle Dai had the heart attack,

30
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:32,400
he didn't take the medicine in time.

31
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:35,250
By the time the doctor arrived,

32
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,579
it was too late.

33
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,640
Dailing.

34
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,850
No matter how you want to take revenge,

35
00:02:58,760 --> 00:02:59,490
don't worry.

36
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,280
I'll be there for you.

37
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,400
What?

38
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,340
After spending a day with Ou Shaowen,

39
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,780
you're disgusted by my approach?

40
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,260
You followed me again.

41
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:04,920
Followed?

42
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,480
Are you saying I don't trust you?

43
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:09,560
Then what is trust?

44
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:15,080
Trust is built on mutual faith,

45
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,680
not at the cost of indulging you

46
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,480
in secretly meeting other men behind my back.

47
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,240
You disappeared for a whole day and night,

48
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,770
not answering calls or replying to messages.

49
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:29,360
Do you know when I saw that photo,

50
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:35,200
how much I wanted to chop him up and feed him to the dogs?

51
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,780
Ou Shaowen and I are just normal friends.

52
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,800
We met and talked normally.

53
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,400
This is my personal freedom.

54
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,860
I am not your property.

55
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,000
I am a person.

56
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,440
We have an agreement.

57
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,409
I risked my life to protect you,

58
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,360
not to watch you

59
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,159
secretly hook up with other men.

60
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,600
You are mine.

61
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,280
I appreciate you saving my life,

62
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:16,850
but you shouldn't keep trapping me with that agreement.

63
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,770
Have you ever really respected me?

64
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,040
This isn't love.

65
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,440
It's kidnapping.

66
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:27,760
Kidnapping?

67
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:39,080
As long as you stay by my side,

68
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:41,280
I'll take that charge.

69
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,210
I'm warning you.

70
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:48,760
If you dare

71
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:51,159
to secretly date other men again,

72
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,220
I can't guarantee I won't do something extreme.

73
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,200
I found a new clue.

74
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,240
Since your father's death

75
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,520
was caused by Ruannila at Danpa's instigation,

76
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,800
then your mother's death

77
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,330
must also be related to her.

78
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,840
My mother did say while she was alive

79
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:38,920
that she caught Ruannila and Danpa having an affair.

80
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,800
I have sent someone to investigate this.

81
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,730
There will be news tomorrow night.

82
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:43,610
See you then.

83
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:58,480
Mr. Ou,

84
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,930
it's hard to get.

85
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,260
You need to pay more this time.

86
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,320
Keep your mouth shut.

87
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,560
Got it. I won't say a word.

88
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:33,480
I investigated everyone related to the Dai family.

89
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,080
This person is the most suspicious.

90
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,010
His name is Wala.

91
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,930
He used to be a security guard at the shipyard.

92
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,740
He died the day after the fire.

93
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:43,770
There is no such coincidence in the world.

94
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,320
Right.

95
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,440
He has a son.

96
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,900
He should know something.

97
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,840
Look at this face.

98
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,420
Look familiar?

99
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:56,240
Aren't you...

100
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,000
Why are you here?

101
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:02,680
Wasan.

102
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,490
His son's name is Wasan.

103
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,800
I've seen him.

104
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,160
After Miss Feifei went home tonight,

105
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,220
she stayed at home.

106
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,920
She just went out to meet Ou Shaowen.

107
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,200
What did they talk about?

108
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,360
I didn't have a chance to get close.

109
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,880
I only vaguely heard a few things.

110
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,610
It seemed to be related to Mr. Danpa and Ruannila.

111
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,970
Okay, send me the location.

112
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:38,799
Wasan.

113
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,730
Why are you here?

114
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:51,120
If you're here as guests,

115
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,240
I'll warmly welcome you.

116
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:53,920
But

117
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,360
if you're here for something else,

118
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,000
sorry,

119
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,760
I don't have time.

120
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,740
We just want to talk to you.

121
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:02,880
Sorry.

122
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,290
What do we do now?

123
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,020
Feifei.

124
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,000
I told you

125
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,080
not to follow me anymore.

126
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,340
Do you not understand?

127
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,560
If he can come, why can't I?

128
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,000
Didn't I tell you

129
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,120
not to be alone with any other men?

130
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:44,280
Do you have to be so hostile?

131
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:52,940
You knew all along that Wasan was the key.

132
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:58,680
Ou Shaowen,

133
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,930
are you out of your mind?

134
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:03,920
What does Wasan have?

135
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,720
The evidence of the cabin arson from back then.

136
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,760
He's a dead man walking.

137
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,960
What makes you think he can

138
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,040
live here safely?

139
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,690
You knew she was Dailing all along.

140
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,640
Yet you just stood by while she dug for the truth.

141
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,480
You think I just stood by?

142
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,600
You watched her risk her life.

143
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,860
I had someone watch her

144
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,920
in case she was being tailed.

145
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,680
I didn't want her to know I sent people to protect her,

146
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:28,080
watching and tailing her.

147
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,210
But you, Ou Shaowen,

148
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:31,840
why do you always bring her

149
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,300
to such dangerous places?

150
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:34,800
Are you crazy?

151
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,700
Let me tell you.

152
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,600
I love her.

153
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,330
I did in the past,

154
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,440
I do now,

155
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,060
and I always

156
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,280
will.

157
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,610
You always hurt her in the name of love.

158
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,320
Five years ago, you were the one

159
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,040
who pushed her off the boat.

160
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,600
Is this your so-called love?

161
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,160
Shut up.

162
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,280
It was an accident.

163
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:55,810
Excuses.

164
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,040
If it weren't for Sister Hua,

165
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:58,440
she'd be a pile of bones now.

166
00:10:58,440 --> 00:10:59,640
Is this your so-called love?

167
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,840
Do you have the right to talk about love?

168
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,130
You're not the only one in pain.

169
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:09,560
What gives you the right to wear it like a badge of honor?
